# --- Neon PostgreSQL (libpq / asyncpg URI) ---
# In Neon: Project → Connect → choose "URI" or "Connection string" for **psql**, NOT the HTTP REST URL.
# Paste the full string here. It already includes sslmode=require.
#
# Wrong:  https://...@neon.tech/...
# Right:  postgresql://YOUR_ROLE:YOUR_PASSWORD@ep-xxx.region.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require
#
# If you still see "user 'user'" in errors, you left the .env.example placeholder — replace USER/PASSWORD
# with the Neon role and password from the dashboard. Special chars in the password must be URL-encoded.
